Steps to Run RSV-v2

Step 1: Trigger via GitHub Actions
Use the GitHub Action workflow to run Terraform for each folder automatically.

Step 2: Configure the File Path
In the workflow file, locate the variable:
yamlTF_DIR: "path/to/your/terraform/folder"

Update TF_DIR to point to the correct Terraform directory as needed.


Step 3: Push the Code
Place your test files in one of the following locations:
LocationDescriptiontests/ folderRecommended location for test filesRoot directoryAlternatively place in the repo rootCustom pathDefine the path explicitly in the workflow TF_DIR variable
bashgit add .
git commit -m "Add RSV-v2 Terraform config"
git push origin main

Step 4: Workflow Executes Automatically
Once the code is pushed:

✅ GitHub Actions triggers the workflow automatically
✅ Terraform runs against the specified TF_DIR
✅ All steps execute in the pipeline


Step 5: Monitor the Logs
View execution logs in real time:

Go to your GitHub repository
Click the Actions tab
Select the latest workflow run
Expand each step to view detailed logs
